Privacy Policy for Hot n Spicy

Effective Date: 22/08/2025

Hot n Spicy respects your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and protect the information of users who use our mobile application Hot n Spicy App

1. Information We Collect

When you use our App, we may collect the following information:

Personal Information: Name, phone number, delivery address, and email address when you place an order.

Order Information: Details of the food items you order, payment method (e.g., cash on delivery, card details if supported).

Location Information (Optional): If you enable location services, we may collect your location to improve delivery accuracy.

2. How We Use Your Information

We use your information to:

Process and deliver your food orders.

Communicate with you about your orders, promotions, or updates.

Ensure security and prevent fraudulent activity.

3. Sharing of Information

We do not sell or share your personal information with third parties for marketing. We may share your information only in the following cases:

Service Providers: With delivery staff, payment processors, or other trusted partners to fulfill your orders.

Legal Requirements: If required by law, regulation, or legal process.

4. Data Security

We use reasonable security measures to protect your personal information. However, please note that no method of electronic transmission is 100% secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.

5. Your Choices

You may update or delete your personal information by contacting us.

You may disable location services in your device settings if you do not want us to collect your location.

You may uninstall the App at any time to stop all collection and use of your information.

6. Childrenâ€™s Privacy

Our App is not intended for children under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children.

7. Changes to this Privacy Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be posted in the App, and the updated version will have a new "Effective Date" at the top.

